        "content": "<p>It seems that <code>ofPPFormat</code> can be used to create a <code>MessageData</code> â€lazilyâ€œ. I expect this would be very useful in tactic code of the form</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">throwError</span> <span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"bp\">!</span><span class=\"s2\">\"foo bar {â† baz}\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>where <code>baz : MetaM MessageData</code> is a possibly expensive operation, and you donâ€™t want to run it unless someone really looks at the message, so that <code>try tac</code> will not spend time assembling the error message.</p>\n<p>But I donâ€™t quite understand the plumbing here. Can one write a </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">lazyMessageData</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">MetaM</span> <span class=\"n\">MessageData</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">MessageData</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>or</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">lazyMessageData</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">MetaM</span> <span class=\"n\">MessageData</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">MetaM</span> <span class=\"n\">MessageData</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>somehow?</p>",
